The paper proposes a model for summarizing scientific articles, which involves analyzing citation summary networks and clustering. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), deep learning (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
